323
00:18:08,629 --> 00:18:10,130
That's a human problem.

324
00:18:10,214 --> 00:18:14,093
So maybe we should consult
our most problematic human.

325
00:18:16,095 --> 00:18:18,013
So, let me get this straight.

326
00:18:18,097 --> 00:18:20,641
You want me to convince Michael
to turn you into a marble

327
00:18:20,724 --> 00:18:22,893
because you're causing earthquakes,

328
00:18:22,976 --> 00:18:26,438
because you're sad about Jason,
to whom you were once married,

329
00:18:26,522 --> 00:18:28,107
because he's currently
sleeping with Tahani?

330
00:18:28,190 --> 00:18:29,483
-Correct.
-I don't think I've ever

331
00:18:29,566 --> 00:18:32,277
meant this literally,
but that might be too much information.

332
00:18:32,361 --> 00:18:35,697
First of all,
I totally get the Jason thing.

333
00:18:35,781 --> 00:18:39,785
He's a ding-dong,
but also a straight hottie, so up top.

334
00:18:40,494 --> 00:18:42,788
But more important,
what you're going through

335
00:18:42,871 --> 00:18:45,040
is something every person
has gone through.

336
00:18:45,124 --> 00:18:45,999
Not a person.

337
00:18:46,083 --> 00:18:48,544
